modules.description: Provides functions to modify specific line ranges in a file, commit changes to disk with optional backup, and reset the current state. Operates on strings, integers representing line numbers, and a custom action type for commit behavior. Used to programmatically edit configuration files by replacing sections and saving updates.

Provides functions to retrieve the version string, optional commit hash, and optional commit date. Works with strings and optional values representing version control metadata. Used to embed build information into applications for debugging or logging purposes.

Processes m4 macro expansions and test cases from GNU Autoconf test suites, executing them in a controlled environment. Operates on structured test data, including macro definitions and test scripts. Enables automated validation of configure scripts during build processes.

manages file editing and version metadata by offering line-range modification, commit control with backup options, and retrieval of version strings, commit hashes, and dates. It handles strings, line numbers, and custom commit actions for file manipulation, and extracts optional metadata for build tracking. Users can replace sections in configuration files and embed build details into applications. Operations include committing changes with rollback capability and accessing version control data for logging.
